entries.femaleVariant: Plan's got a lot of holes. I like it.
It all sounds too simple.
Plan's got more gaping holes than a Kabuki dollhouse.
But fuck it, it's gotta work!
Rogue?
What?
And you, Weyland, heat up the Strix. We'll be with ya soon.
How long you gon' be? Might I have time for a nap? Heheh.
Fucking Christ!
Hahaha! Every time, every time!
What'd I miss? What're you doing here?
Next time, you're losin' teeth.
Think so? I would like to see ya try. But the boss will not be happy when I break your bones.
"Ours"? So you're in?
You're the best.
"Our ride"? So you're in?
You're the best.
Don't act all surprised, leadhead.
'Course I am. Your sorry ass wouldn't be here otherwise.
See you two've said your "hellos." Excellent.
Rogue, what's this specimen doin' here?
He's our pilot and our ride to Corpo Plaza today.
Yep. Jack in the shard.
[Take shard]
Whaddaya think?
See just one problem – there's no comin' back from this. You'll burn bridges.
To ash and dust.
All Arasaka's gonna be gunnin' for you.
Don't mind if I do...
Strap 'em to your legs and you can jump from damn near any height.
Sooo... like this?
Christ, Johnny. I'm not your fucking babysitter.
Never mind. Got it.
Johnny, you'll need gear. Take a look.
Grab some gear, Johnny, don't forget.
Hmm. What're these?
Retrothrusters. Anti-gravs.
There's still the matter of Alt.
Rogue...
Exactly. Then we jump in, find the building's vertical axis and work our way down...
So, summing up – we fly to Arasaka Tower unnoticed and say hello with a welcome basket of missiles.
To the Mikoshi access point, yup.
Say no more!
Not gonna work. We're gonna get shredded.
Love the sentimentality of it – you know how much I love to blow shit up. But I don't think we're gonna survive in there.
Soon as security's alerted, they'll call in Spec Ops, and that's about all she wrote.
No. She didn't.
Sayin' we're gonna rain fire on these assholes? Seriously?
I've waited too long for this!
Don't bust outta your pants just yet.
If we wanna survive, we gotta do a lot more.
I'll convince Alt.
Could be tough. Alt's got NetWatch on her ass.
A contact at Orbital Air, eh?
Got a certain... acquaintance at Orbital Air.
I'm supposed to talk to Alt anyway. I'll convince her.
Can try to sway Alt, but no promises.
Contacts at Orbital Air, eh? You really are the queen of fixers.
I could give a shit about her feelings. I'm the one takin' most of the risks here.
Unfettered AI, remember. She can be... difficult. Still got the Watch on her ass, too.
entries.maleVariant: Unfettered AI, remember? She can be... difficult. Still got the Watch on her ass, too.

entries.femaleVariant: 'Sides, bringin' down a satellite might not make her happy.
Either you convince Cunningham, or I'm out.
I said I'd try! Christ…
I'll pay him enough to give us access to the Juroujin.
Better be grateful. Called on my best assets for you.
Mystery benefactor?
Highly positioned informant.
The rest'll be up to our old netrunner friend.
Don't fuck this up, Johnny. It's the one thing I can't do for you.
You mean Alt.
Only one I know who can rip an Arasaka satellite outta the sky.
Head out back. Nix'll show you the ropes.
Next time, I'll punch some holes in that toothy grin.
Let's go. The boss awaits.
Mean Rogue?
There is only one boss.
Brew all this up while I was asleep?
Actually, I brewed it up while you were dead.
A finger in the comms network pie when corp conflicts start to heat up again could be worth gold.
'Cause nothing stands to make you more eddies than war.
You brew this up while I slept?
Target's the Mikoshi access point in Arasaka Tower.
Need to reach the lab floor, hold it just long enough to do what we need to do, then get out alive.
Arasaka Tower's a fortress, the most secure building in Night City. Walking in through the front door just ain't an option.
So, we'll get in through a window of our own making.
Specifically, we fly in on a Militech Strix tactical bomber.
First, we rain fire on the building's air defenses from a high altitude.
Then, we breach a wall on the seventy-sixth floor, jump from the AV and survive the landing thanks to our anti-gravs.
The shaft runs the height of the building. We use our retrothrusts again, reach the bottom floor quickly.
We hit the lab floor running, reach the access point... the rest'll be in your hands.
I'll hold for applause.
Sheesh, didn't say you had a bomber!
Didn't say you had a bomber!
We'll surprise the socks off security, they'll be in disarray. Resistance should be minimal.

That's right, we'll land smack in the middle of a tropical rainforest. Contrary to popular opinion, Arasaka has... panache, at times. We cut our way through the jungle to a shaft located on the tower's vertical axis.
We all have our secrets.
Guess nowadays a slick, red Mizutani just doesn't cut it... How'd you get that?
I'm the best fixer in town, idiot – 'nuff said. Now focus on the plan.
Here comes the tricky bit.
Buy yourself a space shuttle, too?
Not even gonna ask how.
Mean to tell me that apart from that fuckin' bomber you have a weaponized space shuttle?
I'm not even gonna ask how.
That'll freeze comms in NC, NorCal and SoCal. Should buy us three or four hours.
Said I'd do it and I will.
No coordination, no support. Complete chaos.
Gear's over there. Help yourself.
OK, now, gonna tell me what the plan is?
Do you know how to move around cyberspace?
Well... V got some practice under her belt. Sure I'll manage.
entries.maleVariant: Well... V got some practice under his belt. Sure I'll manage.

entries.femaleVariant: Just... thank you.
I dunno... Sounds too simple somehow.
Thank me later.
Forgot to mention our chances of survival are shit.
And you still wanna--
I do.
End of topic.
Arasaka'll know it was you.
It won't be the stupidest stunt we've ever pulled.
Yeah, probably Orbital Air will too.
But as I see it, they braided this whip that's gonna sting 'em.
So? Whaddaya think?
We're gonna knock a Juroujin-0401 comms sat off its orbit.
Anti-what now?
[Stand]
I remember that face. Gotta be Crispin Weyland. Spitting image of your dad.
Blood of the blood.
But what'd I miss? Why're you here?
The boss will explain all.
Rogue?
There is only one boss.
Never have I seen one not drunk as a pig sleep over twenty hours.
A bloodclaat satellite! We goin' to make history, friends!
As I said, there is only one boss, one queen.
Weren't ya listenin'? We all got work to do. I'll coax the AV to life while you deal with the mad AI from behind the Blackwall. Back to the bar.
